tip.text: Cute tapas place with a solid offering.  Friendly service and nice vibe.  The anchovies were out of this world - salty, briny goodness (if you're into that sort of thing)
Beef cheek and the fried sweetbreads.  Trust me.
Definitely needs a visit if you're in the area - the secreto iberico still has me drooling.
Can't miss the grilled mushrooms with small chunks of iberico ham!
Must agree with everyone else - the pringa montadito is a cannot miss!
Get the chicharrones de Cadiz and orange wine.  You'll thank me later.
Awesome fries. Awesome fries. Awesome fries.  That is all.
Still some of the best wings you can get on Penn campus.  Never disappoints!
View from the balcony overlooking the market was cool but service is super slow.  Bloody Mary was perfection.
Highly ranked for a reason as you can't go wrong with the food but don't miss out on the cocktails.  The steak pie & buttery mash was solid but highlight was the salted caramel espresso martini.
This place was so good and definitely worth a visit - cool vibe, friendly service, and super yum food.  The sea bream was cooked to perfection!
By far the BEST meal in Dubrovnik - super friendly staff, great music & the aroma coming from the kitchen will get you drooling.  Chicken chorizo tacos + swordfish black curry not to be missed.
Must try these wings.  Get the snake in the basket for those who dare - the heat level on the viper may melt your digestive track.
Though more famous for the coffee / desserts, definitely should try the potato pancakes with chicken.  Worth every artery clogging calorie.
Lovely area to stroll and enjoy the weather. Lovely cafes and restaurants along the way in case you want a drink or some nibbles
The short ribs were out of this world - must order! The clams appetisers were also delicious. Can't go wrong here!
You can't order anything wrong here - especially if you always had a soft poached egg to everything!
The fish soup is good (get the large portion of you want some mussels included) but definitely have some oysters.
Reasonable prices for such an expensive city - the dish I had was a tad salty but otherwise very well done. Try to get something off the "hawker" menu if any is left for dinner.
Surprise menu where you simply choose 3 tapas, 5 tapas or 3 tapas + main course. Interesting concept and a friendly staff but overall underwhelmed by the tapas themselves.
The toast skagen was tasty - cute place with lots of history.
Interesting place to visit for history buffs but may come off as underwhelming compared to other European palaces. Crown Jewels do not begin to compare to those in the UK.
Overall was underwhelmed as it seemed like any other cafe - nothing overly memorable. There's a cave downstairs for food tours to have a fika
An obvious touristy spot given its location near the Uffizi but very friendly staff who was more than willing to keep the ice coming during a hot summer afternoon. Coffee slushy is a good choice too
Porchetta is definitely yummy but don't overlook the tripe!  For those ordering the sandwich, you can order extra meat to go with it
Order carefully as some dishes are hit or miss. Crispy pork belly bao is a must; steamed oysters and sugar snap peas were average at best.
The Swedish meatballs do not disappoint! Pull up a bar seat, order a Zinfandel to go with your meal and dig in.
Lovely selection for your meat needs - if you time it right, there are some true exotic choices for picking (think smoked brown bear)
A definite place for cheese lovers and game meat fans. Very friendly & knowledgeable staff!
The Swedish meatballs may not be on the menu but order them anyways - the kitchen is ready to make them upon request!
Must try anything and everything here - the gravlax and matches herring were outstanding! Must also get crayfish when in season.
The "small" tasting menu option was more than filling. Some dishes were hit or miss but overall great experience especially when combined with the wine pairing. Very friendly & attentive staff!
A definite inclusion for any Stockholm visit - very cute place for those looking for a tasty bite. The Swedish chanterelles with potato and cheese purée is amazing.
Such a cute place - everything is tasting menu so choose between 4 / 6 course.  Heavily features veggies that were tasty but the chicken breast w/ wheatberry risotto was the winner of the night
Unabashedly touristy but such a great place for any jamon enthusiast! Friendly staff with decent prices given the location
A carb-lovers dream. Croissants were amazing as was the trdelnik...freshly made on the ground and strangely mesmerising seeing it just rolling along
Awesome cheesesteaks (and cheese fries!) that make you homesick for Philadelphia. You must have yours with the homemade wiz and onions.
Excellent choice if you want a break from the Barca seafood. Rabbit, lamb ribs, roast kid and suckling pig all must haves. Finish off with the Crema Catalan.

formattedAddress: C. Escudellers, 14 (C. Nou de Sant Francesc)

tip.text: Cute pintxos bar to stop by for a quick nibble + drink if you're in the area. Nothing I would go out of my way for to visit.
Foie gras with eggs. No doubt about it. So decadently yummy in your tummy. (Everything else was good too)
Should be on everyone's must visit list! Tuna tartare, kinder egg, foie gras + risotto...all not to be missed! Sous vide veal cheek wasn't my favourite but the rambutan garnish was tasty
Rock Lobster + spiny crab = amazing. They use the roe of the crab to make a crab dip you want to guzzle. Lobster was grilled to perfection.
Worthy inclusion to any tapas list - rabbit ribs, sea bass ceviche, tuna tataki, red mullet and bikini sandwich highly recommended. Skip the chiperones & lamb. Must end with the chocolate mousse!
Chilli crabs were tasty but the white pepper crab and cereal prawn stole the show for me. Bring a group so you can have a legit seafood fest

venue.name: No Signboard Seafood 无招牌海鲜

tip.text: Come for the claypot but stay for the pumpkin clayfish and fried soft shell crab
Decent place for a quick bite in the area - Beirut sandwich was the most popular but only average in my opinion. Pita bread was nice and crunchy though
Had high hopes as menu sounded good but alas, sushi was average and borderline disappointing. Go try somewhere else.

formattedAddress: R. Oscar Freire, 507 (entre R. Pe. João Manuel e R. Augusta)
location.crossStreet: entre R. Pe. João Manuel e R. Augusta

tip.text: Love this place - almond martinis, peppermint martinis, Malbec, chicken lollipops and white truffle pizza do NOT disappoint
The foie a la plantxa and a glass of Emilio Moro.  Amazing combo that won't disappoint.
Ravioli with lamb sweetbreads was also very tasty for those more adventurous
Scallops were very tasty - definitely won't disappoint
Lovely traditional pintxos bar with friendly people - gazpacho was refreshing choice.
The Tarta de Queso is to die for! Best. Cheesecake. EVER. Even if you don't try anything else here, you MUST get that!
Veal cheeks and the pulpo!  The pulpo was one of the best pintxos I've ever tasted. Pass on the orzo risotto - didn't quite hit the spot for me compared to the others.
Molecular gastronomy meets pintxos. Visually appealing and definitely not your traditional pintxos bar if thats what you want. Try the La Hoguera (cod fish)
Must get the "hongos plantxa" (white mushrooms cooked on a grill top) - absolutely amazing taste and texture that can't be replicated.
Bruschetta was a tasty choice for an appetizer.  Pappardelle with funghi was also delish.  Reasonable prices for such a high traffic area.
Great selection of meats and cheeses...prosciutto and mortadella were amazing. Buffalo mozzarella was really fresh.
Best cappuccino in the city - shaved chocolate on top was a nice touch
Head upstairs for the main dining tables as ground floor is just the cafe. Tagliatelle with bolognese did not disappoint!
Sit at the barrel tables outside and have a casual nosh of the cured meats & cheese platter.  Lambrusco is a must for those who like sparkly wine
Great set menu - choice of starter, main and dessert plus beer/wine/soda and coffee - for €19.90.  Arroz Negra and Fideua were personal favourites.  Definitely sit outside and enjoy the breeze!

formattedAddress: Passeig Marítim de la Barceloneta, s/n
location.address: Passeig Marítim de la Barceloneta, s/n

tip.text: You can never go wrong with the razor clams (Navajas) and a glass of Estrella. Makes the hovering / stalking for a seat well worth it
Wouldn't go out of my way to eat here  but decent place to get afternoon tea if you're in the area to see the Tower of London
Red onion and sweetcorn is definitely a not miss!  Super nice staff to boot.  Two slices of pizza and you're ready to roll out the door and take a nap
Crispy plaice smorrebrod - thumbs up
House special BBQ ribs were not bad but not great - massive slab of ribs best washed down with a cold Carlsberg
Room 122 was fun if you don't mind people walking by your windows as the room is in between the ground floor and the 1st floor
Last take away order around 23:40-23:45.  Thumbs up on Vietnamese spicy porkchops even though not that spicy.  Still tasty for under £6
Ramen noodles were nice and chewy but the char siu left much to be desired
Skip the ravioli...but MUST have brownie!  To die for...
Get the fresh fish of the day...grilled to perfection
Black rice and squid had potential but was only passable...maybe bc it wasn't freshly made?
Skip the croquettas...looks good but end up being tasteless fillers
Skip the pescado tacos...looked crispy but was quite soggy
